# Resource safety (mandatory — read before ANY shell command)

**The user cannot message you while the machine is crashing.** Every heavy
command must be safe *before* it starts.

## Exception: CI before commit

**Before `git commit`**, you MUST run `./scripts/ci-local.sh` (full CI parity).
This is the sanctioned full gate — not subject to the single-file test limit
below. Run it once per commit batch; do not parallelize with other heavy jobs.

## Non‑negotiable: use the guard scripts

| Task | Command |
|------|---------|
| Unit tests | `./scripts/agent-safe-test.sh tests/<one-file>.py` |
| Integration (user asked explicitly) | `AGENT_ALLOW_INTEGRATION=1 ./scripts/agent-safe-test.sh tests/integration/<one-file>.py -m integration` |
| Full suite (user asked explicitly) | `AGENT_ALLOW_FULL_SUITE=1 ./scripts/agent-safe-test.sh` |

**Raw `pytest`, `python -m pytest`, and parallel test runs across repos are
FORBIDDEN** unless the user explicitly requested a full suite and
`AGENT_ALLOW_FULL_SUITE=1` is set.

The guard script **refuses to start** when MemAvailable &lt; 2GB or swap &gt; 35%,
caps virtual memory (~3GB), enforces a hard timeout (90s unit / 180s integration),
and blocks integration/full-suite by default.

## One heavy job, ever

- Never run two guarded commands in parallel (tests, pip install, mypy, docker,
  ripgrep over whole repo, Task subagents that scan or test).
- Never chain “public tests then commercial tests” without confirming memory
  recovered (`free -h` — MemAvailable ≥ 2GB, swap not climbing).

## Default verification = one file

After a code change, run **one** test file for the module you touched. Do not
re-run 600+ tests to validate a single fix. Do not run tests at all if the change
is docs-only.

## Search & read

- Grep: always `path` or `glob`; never whole-repo unscoped search.
- Read: `limit` on files &gt; 500 lines. Never load multi‑MB JSON into context.

## pip install

Once per repo per session unless `pyproject.toml` / lockfiles changed.

## If guard refuses

Report the refusal to the user and **stop** — do not bypass with raw pytest.
